about.summary: Clean, simple, and fast access to public hydrology and climatology data

name: ulmo
raw_recipe:
# Jinja variables help maintain the recipe as you'll update the version only here.
{% set version = "0.8.3.2" %}
{% set sha256 = "29a77355b36b2bc77b1486b2f9cb1db2af65a3a0ba83b25b1ac2655b18c4b921" %}

package:
  name: ulmo
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  fn: ulmo-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/u/ulmo/ulmo-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  script: python setup.py install --single-version-externally-managed --record record.txt

requirements:
  build:
    - python
    - setuptools
  run:
    - python
    - appdirs
    - beautifulsoup4
    - future
    - geojson
    - isodate
    - lxml
    - mock
    - numpy
    - pandas
    - pytables
    - pytest
    - requests
    - suds-jurko
    - freezegun
    - html5lib <=0.9999999

test:
  imports:
    - ulmo.usgs.nwis
    - ulmo.cdec.historical
    - ulmo.util
    - ulmo.waterml
    - ulmo.ncdc
    - ulmo.cpc
    - ulmo.cuahsi
    - ulmo.cpc.drought
    - ulmo.ncdc.gsod
    - ulmo.usgs.eddn
    - ulmo.ncdc.cirs
    - ulmo.twc
    - ulmo.cuahsi.his_central
    - ulmo.usgs
    - ulmo.usace.rivergages
    - ulmo
    - ulmo.ncdc.ghcn_daily
    - ulmo.usace.swtwc
    - ulmo.twc.kbdi
    - ulmo.cuahsi.wof
    - ulmo.usace
    - ulmo.cdec
    - ulmo.nasa
    - ulmo.lcra

about:
  home: https://github.com/ulmo-dev/ulmo
  license: BSD 3-Clause
  summary: 'Clean, simple, and fast access to public hydrology and climatology data'
  doc_url: http://ulmo.readthedocs.io/
  dev_url: https://github.com/ulmo-dev/ulmo/

extra:
  recipe-maintainers:
    - ocefpaf
    - dharhas
